The subject of finance and financial environment. Time value of money. Analysis of financial instruments. Bank services. Investment process and strategies. Financial investments.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing the students with the basic knowledge, terminology and specificity of finance, practical skills (e.g. analytics, problem solving) for financing to enhance wealth and entrepreneurship.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course  the student knows  the main concepts of personal finance incl concepts of time value of money, main concepts od financial math, types of stock and opportunities for financing a company, terminology and services of commercial banking and investment banking and Estonian financial environment (incl finacial markets). After passing the course, the student is able to make justified financial choices in personal life, make simple financial math calculations with PDA and MS Excel, calculate the value of stock, profitablity, price and risk, compile and analyse the graphs of loan and lease, make currency calculations and evaluate credit cost rate when financing and evaluate the income, cost, profit and profitability and taxes.
